": \"back pain\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 680}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ethiopia's Tamirat Tola took the gold, finishing first by a wide margin, while Belgium's Bashir Abdi won silver and Benson Kipruto secured Kenya a spot on the podium by earning bronze.\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 905, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 721, \"end\": 729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999984203544698, \"rank\": 1.5795907813440298e-06, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 732, \"end\": 744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamirat_Tola\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tamirat Tola\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamirat_Tola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamirat_Tola\"}, {\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999679975949645, \"rank\": 1.6212767549283124e-05, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 810, \"end\": 821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bashir_Abdi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bashir Abdi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bashir_Abdi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bashir_Abdi\"}, {\"begin\": 837, \"end\": 851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benson_Kipruto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Benson Kipruto\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benson_Kipruto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benson_Kipruto\"}, {\"begin\": 860, \"end\": 865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999927035788, \"rank\": 7.271901181564461e-09, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the gold\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 758}, {\"ngram\": \"a wide margin\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 792}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 832}, {\"ngram\": \"a spot\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 872}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 886}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 904}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In typical sanguine fashion, Kipchoge downplayed the defeat - the first time he has not finished a race - and did not give any hints as to his widely-expected retirement from the sport.\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 1092, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"typical sanguine fashion\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 934}, {\"ngram\": \"Kipchoge\", \"from\": 936, \"to\": 944}, {\"ngram\": \"the defeat\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 966}, {\"ngram\": \"a race\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1010}, {\"ngram\": \"any hints\", \"from\": 1030, \"to\": 1039}, {\"ngram\": \"his widely-expected retirement\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1076}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1091}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Today is a tough day in my office.\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1129, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Today\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1100}, {\"ngram\": \"a tough day\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"my office\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1128}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As always, you can not predict what will happen,\\\" he told reporters with a smile, adding that he felt supported by the crowds even after slowing to a walk in what he described as his worst-ever race.\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1329, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"reporters\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1197}, {\"ngram\": \"a smile\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1210}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowds\", \"from\": 1245, \"to\": 1255}, {\"ngram\": \"a walk\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1284}, {\"ngram\": \"his worst-ever race\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1328}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I walked for two kilometers and I had more than 300 people on my side walking together,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1429, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two kilometers\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1359}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 300 people\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1390}, {\"ngram\": \"my side\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1401}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Passing runners, too, were encouraging him to keep pushing on, he said.\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"runners\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1446}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I could feel the love and the respect, actually.\\\"\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1553, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the love\", \"from\": 1517, \"to\": 1525}, {\"ngram\": \"the respect\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1541}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After stopping Kipchoge took off his running shoes and gave them to a fan before climbing into an official vehicle.\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1670, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Kipchoge\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"his running shoes\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"a fan\", \"from\": 1623, \"to\": 1628}, {\"ngram\": \"an official vehicle\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1669}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Kenyan has four of the 10 fastest marathon times in history, but his personal best of 2:01:09 was nearly two years ago at the 2022 Berlin marathon.\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1823, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1807, \"end\": 1822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin_Marathon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Berlin marathon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin_Marathon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin_Marathon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Kenyan\", \"from\": 1672, \"to\": 1682}, {\"ngram\": \"the 10 fastest marathon times\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1724}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1735}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has won that marathon a record five times and the London marathon four times, but has started to show signs of strain in more recent major races, finishing 10th at the Tokyo marathon in March where compatriot Benson Kipruto won.\", \"from\": 1825, \"to\": 2056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1878, \"end\": 1893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Marathon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London marathon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Marathon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_Marathon\"}, {\"begin\": 1996, \"end\": 2010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_Marathon\", \"score\": 0.9999997886118531, \"rank\": 2.1138818666260923e-07, \"text\": \"Tokyo marathon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_Marathon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_Marathon\"}, {\"begin\": 2037, \"end\": 2051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benson_Kipruto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Benson Kipruto\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benson_Kipruto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benson_Kipruto\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that marathon\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1849}, {\"ngram\": \"a record\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1858}, {\"ngram\": \"signs\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1935}, {\"ngram\": \"strain\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 1945}, {\"ngram\": \"more recent major races\", \"from\": 1949, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 2014, \"to\": 2019}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not know what my future holds,\\\" Kipchoge told reporters after Saturday's race.\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2142, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": 